Comment Posted Oct. 10, 2015 at 1:10 PM Updated at 4:03 PM Posted Oct. 10, 2015 at 1:10 PM Updated at 4:03 PM Â» Social News More mysteries (and more tattoos) are coming to NBC. The network has given Blindspot a full season order two weeks after calling for more scripts of the drama, according to The Hollywood Reporter . The news makes Blindspot the first freshman series of the season to nab a full season. The series stars Jaimie Alexander as an amnesiac Jane Doe whose collection of tattoos help the FBI solve cases, though something bigger than just ink is going on. Blindspot pulled in 10.6 million total viewers with its series premiere, and a 3.1 rating in the coveted 18-49 adult demographic, the highest rating for the network in its timeslot since The Blacklist 's season premiere last year. Are you happy to have more Blindspot this season? Blindspot airs Mondays at 10/9c on NBC.
